Package: PyR
Type: Package
Title: Set of Functions to Allow Use of Python in R
Version: 0.3.2
Date: 2015-07-01
Authors@R: person("Alexander", "Bessonov", email = "nonsleepr@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A bridge between R and Python. Thes package is inspired by rPython
    package but adds some additional functionality like dealing with Python
    exceptions and converting native Python data types to native R data types.
    The pacakge was also inspired by http://gallery.rcpp.org/articles/rcpp-python/ .
URL: https://github.com/nonsleepr/PyR
BugReports: https://github.com/nonsleepr/PyR/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 0.11.6),
    jsonlite (>= 0.9.16)
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 2.7), python-dev (deb)
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
Suggests: testthat
